f oestrogen and progesterone on gonadotropin secretion during the luteal phase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inhibition of LH and stimulation of FSH","Stimulation of LH and inhibition of FSH","Stimulation of LH and FSH","Inhibition of LH and FSH","No effect on LH or FSH"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring the luteal phase of the menstrual cycle, both oestrogen and progesterone exert negative feedback effects on the hypothalamus and anterior pituitary. This results in \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibition of LH and FSH\u003C/strong\u003E secretion. This is different from the follicular phase where low levels of oestrogen alone provide negative feedback, while high levels can trigger positive feedback leading to the LH surge.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of LH and stimulation of FSH\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur as both gonadotropins are suppressed\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulation of LH and inhibition of FSH\u003C/strong\u003E is physiologically incorrect\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulation of LH and FSH\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during the follicular phase with rising oestrogen levels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo effect on LH or FSH\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as there is clear negative feedback\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["During the luteal phase, both oestrogen and progesterone provide negative feedback to inhibit luteinizing hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) secretion.","Negative feedback control of gonadotropins is essential for normal menstrual cycle regulation."],"references":["Hamilton KJ, Hewitt SC, Arao Y, Korach KS. Estrogen Hormone Biology. Curr Top Dev Biol. 2017;125:109-146. doi: 10.1016/bs.ctdb.2016.12.005. Epub 2017 Feb 3. PMID: 28527569; PMCID: PMC6206851.","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA","Kovacs, W. J., \u0026 Ojeda, S. R. (Eds.). (2012). Textbook of endocrine physiology. OUP USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47682"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15685"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47682","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47682"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T13:10:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T19:45:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8376"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62236"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt"